{"pageProps":{"author":"Rebecca Black","articles":[{"title":"Roommate Horror Stories","category":"Nexustentialism","subcategory":"Nexustentialism","publish_date":"2015-09-02T07:00:00.000Z","full_thumbnail":"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/080824unknown2.jpg?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1","mobile_thumbnail":"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/080824unknown2.jpg?resize=500%2C333&ssl=1","description":"The leases are signed, the dorm placements are finalized and it’s the time of year where everyone still has naive optimism about the people they are living with.","content":"<div class=\"single-post-content\">\n            <p>The leases are signed, the dorm placements are finalized and it’s the time of year where everyone still has naive optimism about the people they are living with. Fear not, it’s time to destroy this famed optimism by reading these tragic real-life experiences of a few unlucky folks who were once in your shoes, and made it out only by the skin of their renter’s agreement.</p>\n<p><em>Any resemblance to real roommates, living or dead, is purely coincidental. Unless you recognize yourself in one of these stories — then it’s definitely about you.</em></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_64618\" style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-64618\" data-attachment-id=\"64618\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2015-09-02/roommate-horror-stories/100_8817/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/100_8817.jpg?fit=2304%2C1728&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2304,1728\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"2.8\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"KODAK DX6490 ZOOM DIGITAL CAMERA\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"1093853220\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"6.3\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0.05\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"1\"}' data-image-title=\"100_8817\" data-image-description=\"\" dat